        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
the Garden City Airport, moving northeast at 15 mph. Another strong
thunderstorm was located 8 miles north of the Garden City Airport,
also moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Pierceville around 550 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for
southwestern Kansas.</instruction>
